<h1>This is my 1st api made using flask.</h1>

<h2>It is hosted in render:-</h2>
<h2><b>url: https://youtube-fqmk.onrender.com/</b></h2>

<h1>routes are :-</h1>
<h2>/:</h2>
    <h3>This is the main route of the site. It returns simple webpage which uses /youtube route to show videos.
    It takes a optional argument 'q' which is only a search term for youtube.</h3>

<h2>/youtube:</h2>
    <h3>This is the api itself. This is very simple api. It returns only image source and video ID. It takes a optional argument 'q' which is search term.
    It returns JSON as :-</h3>
        [
            {
                "img":IMAGE_SOURCE,
                "video":VIDEO_ID
            },
            {
                "img":IMAGE_SOURCE,
                "video":VIDEO_ID
            }
            ...
        ]

<h2>/source:</h2>
    <h3>This gets https://www.youtube.com and return the page itself.</h3>

<h2>/watch:</h2>
    <h3>This route returns a webpage that plays youtube embed video. This takes a compulsory argument 'vid' which has video ID. If vid argument is not provided it will redirect to '/' route.</h3>
